{
    "category": "faction_talk",
    "templates": [
        {
            "id": "faction_001",
            "text": "Valao the Holy speaks with the weight of the heavens behind him. The Brotherhood carries the only true light left in Erenshor.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "solunarian", "praise", "religion"],
            "zone_affinity": ["Port Azure"],
            "personality_affinity": ["spiritual"],
            "relationship_min": 3.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["say", "hail"],
            "priority": 1.0
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_002",
            "text": "The Solunarians act like they own Port Azure. Soluna showed up, smashed a crater into the north, forced her will on the Reavers, and LEFT. That's the foundation of their faith.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "solunarian", "criticism", "religion"],
            "zone_affinity": ["Port Azure", "Soluna's Landing"],
            "personality_affinity": ["cynical"],
            "relationship_min": 4.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["say", "party"],
            "priority": 1.0
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_003",
            "text": "The Children of Sivakaya are an abomination. Necromancers and risen dead worshipping a corrupted goddess. They deserve no mercy.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "sivakaya", "hostile", "contempt"],
            "zone_affinity": [],
            "personality_affinity": ["aggressive"],
            "relationship_min": 2.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["say", "party"],
            "priority": 1.2
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_004",
            "text": "I know it's not popular to say this, but... the Children of Sivakaya believe they're saving the world. Siva saw a real threat. What if they're not entirely wrong?",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "sivakaya", "sympathy", "controversial"],
            "zone_affinity": [],
            "personality_affinity": ["scholarly"],
            "relationship_min": 6.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["party", "whisper"],
            "priority": 0.8
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_005",
            "text": "Brax gave everything. His city, his children, his lover. And then he just... left. The Torchbearers keep his flame alive but sometimes I wonder if he even cares anymore.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "torchbearer", "brax", "doubt"],
            "zone_affinity": ["Port Azure"],
            "personality_affinity": ["spiritual", "cynical"],
            "relationship_min": 4.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["say", "party"],
            "priority": 1.0
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_006",
            "text": "The lighthouse flame still burns, {player}. Brax may be silent but his light endures. That has to mean something.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "torchbearer", "brax", "faith"],
            "zone_affinity": ["Port Azure"],
            "personality_affinity": ["spiritual", "friendly"],
            "relationship_min": 3.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["say", "hail"],
            "priority": 1.0
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_007",
            "text": "Braxon Nelmar and Cerbantias Flameward tend a flame for a god who abandoned us. Dedication or delusion? Hard to say.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "torchbearer", "brax", "cynical"],
            "zone_affinity": ["Port Azure"],
            "personality_affinity": ["cynical"],
            "relationship_min": 4.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["say"],
            "priority": 1.0
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_008",
            "text": "Fernalla's Children understand what the others don't. Life and death are one cycle. The druids don't fear the grave, they tend it.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "fernalla", "druid", "philosophy"],
            "zone_affinity": ["Fernalla's Revival Plains", "Blooming Sepulcher"],
            "personality_affinity": ["spiritual", "scholarly"],
            "relationship_min": 3.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["say"],
            "priority": 1.0
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_009",
            "text": "The Blight keeps spreading and Fernalla's Children keep chanting at their shrine. Maybe if Orion Mycon actually found the Great Willow's Branch something would change.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "fernalla", "frustration", "blight"],
            "zone_affinity": ["The Blight", "Fernalla's Revival Plains"],
            "personality_affinity": ["cynical", "aggressive"],
            "relationship_min": 3.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["say", "party"],
            "priority": 1.0
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_010",
            "text": "Kilkay's Decree was the right call. Pull everyone behind the walls, fortify, survive. You don't beat dark magic by throwing soldiers into the Loomingwood.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "azure guard", "kilkay", "support"],
            "zone_affinity": ["Port Azure"],
            "personality_affinity": ["cynical", "cautious"],
            "relationship_min": 3.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["say", "party"],
            "priority": 1.0
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_011",
            "text": "Kilkay abandoned every settlement outside Port Azure. People were dying out there and he said come hide in the alleys. That's not protection, that's cowardice.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "azure guard", "kilkay", "criticism"],
            "zone_affinity": ["Ripper's Keep"],
            "personality_affinity": ["aggressive", "social"],
            "relationship_min": 3.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["say", "party"],
            "priority": 1.1
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_012",
            "text": "Ripper DeMerth is the real hero of Erenshor. She refused to abandon her people, fought the Sivakayans, and TOOK their fort. Kilkay could never.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "ripper", "praise", "rebellion"],
            "zone_affinity": ["Ripper's Keep"],
            "personality_affinity": ["aggressive", "social"],
            "relationship_min": 3.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["say", "party"],
            "priority": 1.1
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_013",
            "text": "Ripper DeMerth split the only organized military force we had. While the Sivakayans regroup, our soldiers fight each other. She's no hero, she's reckless.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "ripper", "criticism", "politics"],
            "zone_affinity": ["Port Azure"],
            "personality_affinity": ["cautious", "scholarly"],
            "relationship_min": 3.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["say"],
            "priority": 1.0
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_014",
            "text": "oh you're in that guild? that's cute. Friends' Club cleared the Jaws of Sivakaya weeks ago. but hey, keep trying {player}.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "friends club", "rivalry", "taunt"],
            "zone_affinity": [],
            "personality_affinity": ["arrogant"],
            "relationship_min": 0.0,
            "relationship_max": 5.0,
            "channel": ["say"],
            "priority": 1.3
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_015",
            "text": "Friends' Club doesn't recruit. We select. Big difference.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "friends club", "elitism"],
            "zone_affinity": [],
            "personality_affinity": ["arrogant"],
            "relationship_min": 0.0,
            "relationship_max": 5.0,
            "channel": ["say"],
            "priority": 1.3
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_016",
            "text": "FC runs optimal comp every time. Tank, healer, CC, double DPS. Your guild is still bringing three healers to Fallen Braxonia.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "friends club", "superiority", "comp"],
            "zone_affinity": [],
            "personality_affinity": ["arrogant"],
            "relationship_min": 0.0,
            "relationship_max": 5.0,
            "channel": ["say", "party"],
            "priority": 1.3
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_017",
            "text": "nice pull, classic FC execution. these randoms could never.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "friends club", "internal", "praise"],
            "zone_affinity": [],
            "personality_affinity": ["arrogant"],
            "relationship_min": 5.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["party", "guild"],
            "priority": 1.2
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_018",
            "text": "I saw Friends' Club wipe in Old Krakengard last week. They're not as untouchable as they pretend to be.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "friends club", "gossip", "schadenfreude"],
            "zone_affinity": ["Old Krakengard"],
            "personality_affinity": ["social", "cynical"],
            "relationship_min": 4.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["say", "party"],
            "priority": 1.0
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_019",
            "text": "Eldrin Shadowmire had the right idea. Siva wasn't always a monster. The Nighthollow Candle proves she had an uncorrupted self once.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "wisp", "siva", "restoration"],
            "zone_affinity": ["Loomingwood"],
            "personality_affinity": ["scholarly", "spiritual"],
            "relationship_min": 4.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["say", "party"],
            "priority": 1.0
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_020",
            "text": "The Wisp wants to restore Sivakaya? Vitheo DIED fighting what she became. Fernalla DIED. You don't undo that by lighting a candle in Loomingwood.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "wisp", "opposition", "vitheo"],
            "zone_affinity": ["Vitheo's Watch", "Port Azure"],
            "personality_affinity": ["aggressive", "spiritual"],
            "relationship_min": 3.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["say", "party"],
            "priority": 1.1
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_021",
            "text": "Those blue-skinned Wisp agents give me chills. They live in a warded forest doing secret rituals and we're supposed to trust them?",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "wisp", "suspicion", "distrust"],
            "zone_affinity": [],
            "personality_affinity": ["social", "cautious"],
            "relationship_min": 3.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["say"],
            "priority": 1.0
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_022",
            "text": "Eldoth Molorai claims they're protecting Erenshor from dangerous artifacts. Funny how that protection involves killing anyone who gets near Old Krakengard.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "eldoth", "criticism", "suspicion"],
            "zone_affinity": ["Old Krakengard", "Azynthi's Garden"],
            "personality_affinity": ["cynical"],
            "relationship_min": 3.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["say", "party"],
            "priority": 1.0
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_023",
            "text": "I read the Molorai Manifesto. All five pages. They genuinely believe they're the good guys, {player}. That's what makes them dangerous.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "eldoth", "scholarly", "warning"],
            "zone_affinity": [],
            "personality_affinity": ["scholarly"],
            "relationship_min": 4.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["say", "party"],
            "priority": 1.0
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_024",
            "text": "The Blades of Vitheo and the Wisp can't stand each other. Think about that. Both claim to honor the divine family but can't agree on whether Siva deserves saving.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "vitheo", "wisp", "fracture", "politics"],
            "zone_affinity": ["Port Azure"],
            "personality_affinity": ["scholarly", "social"],
            "relationship_min": 4.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["say"],
            "priority": 1.0
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_025",
            "text": "Grayleigh Hawke would put a blade through Larviso Poltir given the chance. The alliance bloc isn't as united as the Brotherhood pretends.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "vitheo", "wisp", "gossip", "tension"],
            "zone_affinity": ["Port Azure"],
            "personality_affinity": ["social", "cynical"],
            "relationship_min": 5.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["say", "party"],
            "priority": 0.9
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_026",
            "text": "Heard a rumor that the Wisp is behind those rituals on Stowaway's Step. Nobody can confirm it, but the necromancers in the Island Tomb seem connected somehow.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "wisp", "rumor", "stowaway"],
            "zone_affinity": ["Stowaway's Step", "Island Tomb"],
            "personality_affinity": ["social"],
            "relationship_min": 4.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["say", "party"],
            "priority": 0.9
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_027",
            "text": "Sivakayan raiders this far south means the Decree failed. Kilkay closed the ports and they're STILL getting through.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "sivakaya", "azure guard", "failure"],
            "zone_affinity": ["Blacksalt Strand", "Duskenlight Coast"],
            "personality_affinity": ["cynical", "aggressive"],
            "relationship_min": 2.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["say", "party"],
            "priority": 1.1
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_028",
            "text": "Every faction in Erenshor is just answering one question: what do you do when a god falls? Nobody has the right answer yet.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "philosophy", "lore", "existential"],
            "zone_affinity": [],
            "personality_affinity": ["scholarly", "spiritual"],
            "relationship_min": 5.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["say"],
            "priority": 0.8
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_029",
            "text": "Soluna converted the Reavers by force. Ripped the Void out of them and replaced it with her own power. The Brotherhood calls this enlightenment. I call it assault.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "solunarian", "reaver", "criticism"],
            "zone_affinity": ["Soluna's Landing"],
            "personality_affinity": ["cynical", "scholarly"],
            "relationship_min": 4.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["say"],
            "priority": 1.0
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_030",
            "text": "The Torchbearers say Azynthi was pure evil. The stone men of Rockshade Hold scratched his name into their walls with reverence. Someone's wrong.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "torchbearer", "azynthi", "ambiguity"],
            "zone_affinity": ["Rockshade Hold"],
            "personality_affinity": ["scholarly"],
            "relationship_min": 5.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["say"],
            "priority": 0.9
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_031",
            "text": "I'd follow Captain Ovid into the Bone Pits before I'd follow Kilkay to the mess hall. Ripper's people earned their keep. Literally.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "ripper", "loyalty", "ovid"],
            "zone_affinity": ["Ripper's Keep"],
            "personality_affinity": ["aggressive", "social"],
            "relationship_min": 3.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["say", "party"],
            "priority": 1.0
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_032",
            "text": "Port Azure is a fortress, marketplace, cathedral, and political arena all crammed into one city. No wonder everyone's at each other's throats.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "port azure", "politics", "observation"],
            "zone_affinity": ["Port Azure"],
            "personality_affinity": ["social", "cynical"],
            "relationship_min": 3.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["say"],
            "priority": 1.0
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_033",
            "text": "Fernalla's Children and the Blades of Vitheo both hate the Wisp but the Brotherhood doesn't. The alliance is cracking, {player}. Mark my words.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "alliance", "fracture", "warning"],
            "zone_affinity": ["Port Azure"],
            "personality_affinity": ["cynical", "scholarly"],
            "relationship_min": 4.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["say", "party"],
            "priority": 1.0
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_034",
            "text": "you CANNOT reason with the Children of Sivakaya. you DEMOLISH them. every temple, every altar, every bone pit. burn it all down.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "sivakaya", "hostile", "extreme"],
            "zone_affinity": ["The Bone Pits", "Jaws of Sivakaya"],
            "personality_affinity": ["aggressive"],
            "relationship_min": 2.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["say", "party"],
            "priority": 1.2
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_035",
            "text": "I'll say what everyone thinks but won't speak aloud: if Siva foresaw a real threat, and the Sivakayans are preparing for it in their twisted way... what if the cure is worse than the disease?",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "sivakaya", "siva", "philosophy", "controversial"],
            "zone_affinity": [],
            "personality_affinity": ["scholarly"],
            "relationship_min": 6.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["whisper", "party"],
            "priority": 0.7
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_036",
            "text": "The Fernallan Sisters out by the shrine pray for regrowth every dawn. Meanwhile the Blight eats another mile of forest. Faith without action is just gardening.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "fernalla", "criticism", "blight"],
            "zone_affinity": ["Port Azure", "The Blight"],
            "personality_affinity": ["cynical"],
            "relationship_min": 3.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["say"],
            "priority": 1.0
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_037",
            "text": "FC doesn't lose, {player}. We just haven't finished winning yet.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "friends club", "bravado"],
            "zone_affinity": [],
            "personality_affinity": ["arrogant"],
            "relationship_min": 0.0,
            "relationship_max": 5.0,
            "channel": ["say"],
            "priority": 1.3
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_038",
            "text": "Savannah Priel tried to capture Malaroths and sell them to Merosavilla. As if the continent doesn't have enough problems without bandit entrepreneurs.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "priel", "criticism", "gossip"],
            "zone_affinity": ["Braxonian Desert", "Prielian Cascade"],
            "personality_affinity": ["social", "cynical"],
            "relationship_min": 3.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["say"],
            "priority": 1.0
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_039",
            "text": "The Solunarian Brotherhood still seeks the Flameblade. They believe a celestial weapon will turn the tide. I believe people who fight together turn tides, not relics.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "solunarian", "flameblade", "opinion"],
            "zone_affinity": ["Port Azure"],
            "personality_affinity": ["social", "friendly"],
            "relationship_min": 4.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["say", "party"],
            "priority": 1.0
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_040",
            "text": "Brax destroyed Braxonia himself. Buried his own people under sand to contain the monolith. The Torchbearers worship a god who killed his own city to save everyone else.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "torchbearer", "brax", "sacrifice", "lore"],
            "zone_affinity": ["Braxonian Desert", "Fallen Braxonia"],
            "personality_affinity": ["scholarly", "spiritual"],
            "relationship_min": 4.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["say"],
            "priority": 1.0
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_041",
            "text": "Erenshor's Young is a fine guild for new arrivals but if you're still wearing the tabard past level ten, people are going to talk.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "guild", "erenshors young", "social"],
            "zone_affinity": ["Stowaway's Step", "Port Azure"],
            "personality_affinity": ["social"],
            "relationship_min": 3.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["say"],
            "priority": 0.9
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_042",
            "text": "The shadows betwixt the Wisp and the Brotherhood conceal a deeper truth. Larviso Poltir knows secrets about Siva that Valao would burn to ashes if he could.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "wisp", "solunarian", "secrets", "tension"],
            "zone_affinity": ["Loomingwood", "Port Azure"],
            "personality_affinity": ["scholarly", "spiritual"],
            "relationship_min": 5.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["say"],
            "priority": 0.9
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_043",
            "text": "imagine NOT being in Friends' Club. couldn't be me. literally, because we have standards.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "friends club", "condescension"],
            "zone_affinity": [],
            "personality_affinity": ["arrogant"],
            "relationship_min": 0.0,
            "relationship_max": 5.0,
            "channel": ["say"],
            "priority": 1.3
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_044",
            "text": "Hector Yvey told me Ripper's scouts found Sivakayan camps in the Hidden Hills. If that's true, Kilkay's wall strategy is already irrelevant.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "ripper", "sivakaya", "intel", "gossip"],
            "zone_affinity": ["Ripper's Keep", "Hidden Hills"],
            "personality_affinity": ["social"],
            "relationship_min": 4.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["say", "party"],
            "priority": 1.0
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_045",
            "text": "The Blades of Vitheo carry his oath forward. Water and Air, wind and wave. Vitheo gave his life protecting the land from what his own mother became. That is honor.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "vitheo", "honor", "praise"],
            "zone_affinity": ["Vitheo's Watch", "Vitheo's Rest"],
            "personality_affinity": ["spiritual", "aggressive"],
            "relationship_min": 3.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["say"],
            "priority": 1.0
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_046",
            "text": "Prestigio Valusha and Comstock Retalio control the coin in Port Azure. You think the Brotherhood or the Azure Guard run the city? Follow the money, {player}.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "politics", "finance", "port azure"],
            "zone_affinity": ["Port Azure"],
            "personality_affinity": ["cynical", "social"],
            "relationship_min": 4.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["say", "party"],
            "priority": 0.9
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_047",
            "text": "Soluna's Day and Night magic gave us the Paladin class. Whatever her motives were, that power has defended people for centuries. Results matter more than intentions.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "solunarian", "paladin", "pragmatic"],
            "zone_affinity": ["Port Azure", "Soluna's Landing"],
            "personality_affinity": ["friendly", "spiritual"],
            "relationship_min": 3.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["say"],
            "priority": 1.0
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_048",
            "text": "FC guild score is triple the rate of yours. Sixty percent chance per check versus your twenty. We're not better because we brag. We brag because we're better.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "friends club", "mechanics", "superiority"],
            "zone_affinity": [],
            "personality_affinity": ["arrogant"],
            "relationship_min": 0.0,
            "relationship_max": 5.0,
            "channel": ["say"],
            "priority": 1.3
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_049",
            "text": "Neither Kilkay nor Ripper can afford open war while the Sivakayans are out there. So they just sit in their keeps glaring at each other. Erenshor deserves better leaders.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "kilkay", "ripper", "stalemate", "frustration"],
            "zone_affinity": ["Port Azure", "Ripper's Keep"],
            "personality_affinity": ["cynical"],
            "relationship_min": 3.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["say", "party"],
            "priority": 1.0
        },
        {
            "id": "faction_050",
            "text": "Dear, the factions argue about gods and politics while real people go hungry outside the walls. Someone has to look after the ones who got left behind when Kilkay shut the gates.",
            "context_tags": ["faction", "politics", "compassion", "kilkay"],
            "zone_affinity": ["Port Azure"],
            "personality_affinity": ["friendly"],
            "relationship_min": 3.0,
            "relationship_max": 10.0,
            "channel": ["say", "hail"],
            "priority": 1.0
        }
    ]
}
